0260621154331.png&quot;&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[Pasted image 20260621154205]]></title><description><![CDATA[<img src="root/bin/pasted-image-20260621154205.png" target="_self">]]></description><link>root/bin/pasted-image-20260621154205.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">root/Bin/Pasted image 20260621154205.png</guid><pubDate>Sun, 21 Jun 2026 13:42:06 GMT</pubDate><enclosure url="root/bin/pasted-image-20260621154205.png" length="0" type="image/png"/><content:encoded>&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;root/bin/pasted-image-20260621154205.png&quot;&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[Pasted image 20260621153043]]></title><description><![CDATA[<img src="root/bin/pasted-image-20260621153043.png" target="_self">]]></description><link>root/bin/pasted-image-20260621153043.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">root/Bin/Pasted image 20260621153043.png</guid><pubDate>Sun, 21 Jun 2026 13:30:43 GMT</pubDate><enclosure url="root/bin/pasted-image-20260621153043.png" length="0" type="image/png"/><content:encoded>&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;root/bin/pasted-image-20260621153043.png&quot;&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[Pasted image 20260621153028]]></title><description><![CDATA[<img src="root/bin/pasted-image-20260621153028.png" target="_self">]]></description><link>root/bin/pasted-image-20260621153028.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">root/Bin/Pasted image 20260621153028.png</guid><pubDate>Sun, 21 Jun 2026 13:30:28 GMT</pubDate><enclosure url="root/bin/pasted-image-20260621153028.png" length="0" type="image/png"/><content:encoded>&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;root/bin/pasted-image-20260621153028.png&quot;&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[Learning ressource-ing clusterfuck]]></title><description><![CDATA[Wavedash, Waveland, Tecking, Wave cancellingWhat are they, How can they work in 3D A Wave Dash is a physics engine exploit achieved by executing a short hop immediately followed by a dash. It manipulates the game's movement calculations, forcing arcing traversal rather than a standard straight dash. It grants massive speeds and range, making it crucial for competitive mobility.Arcs are a very important principle in animation. Wave dashes should be an integral part of the game, easy and comfortable to perform with animations specifically made for the mechanic.<img alt="396" src="https://www.ssbwiki.com/images/6/67/Wavedashing.gif?49709" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" target="_self" class="is-unresolved">Tecking walls and surfaces in Platform fighters is the act of using the environment for the players advantageWhen a character interacts with a surface (a wall, ceiling, floor, or corner), the game registers a specific collision state. A skilled player can use this interaction to control how a character's velocity and trajectory change upon impact.Tecking involves:Wall Jumps/Wall Kicks: Instead of running into a wall, the player initiates an impulse force away from it by jumping or attacking while touching the surface. This allows rapid propulsion upward (Wall Jump) or sideways (Wall Kick). For example, launching diagonally off a vertical wall bypasses opponents positioned directly in front.Edge Guarding/Surface Trapping: The player forces the opponent into a specific position relative to a surface—often at an edge or corner—and then dictates their fate by moving along that surface. By outpacing the trapped opponent (e.g., running along a ceiling), the attacker can initiate a ledge grab or force them into a disadvantageous spot.Every interaction serves a strategic purpose:When hit or knocked back, a player can "teck" themselves into a corner or against a wall to stabilize their trajectory, preventing them from being immediately pushed off the stage (a process known as recovery). They use the surface's resistance to arrest unwanted movement.Wavelanding is similar to/the same as wavedashing with one key differenceThe idea of wavelanding is to wavedash into the ground in the fastest way for an easy and quick follow up attack on the ground.Wave cancelling is the act of cancelling a wavedash]]></description><link>root/f4e/learning-ressource-ing-clusterfuck.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">root/F4E/Learning ressource-ing clusterfuck.md</guid><pubDate>Thu, 04 Jun 2026 11:44:37 GMT</pubDate><enclosure url="https://www.ssbwiki.com/images/6/67/Wavedashing.gif?49709" length="0" type="false"/><content:encoded>&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://www.ssbwiki.com/images/6/67/Wavedashing.gif?49709&quot;&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[Kemuri]]></title><description><![CDATA[Monster hunter like Multiplayer Yokai hunting game with Director of BayonettaIt has an awesome aesthetic and world. The yokai can be slain and used as abillitys wich is visualized by fashionable clothing]]></description><link>root/kemuri.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">root/Kemuri.md</guid><pubDate>Thu, 04 Jun 2026 00:28:42 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Platform fighter established competitive mechanics]]></title><link>root/f4e/platform-fighter-established-competitive-mechanics.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">root/F4E/Platform fighter established competitive mechanics.md</guid><pubDate>Thu, 04 Jun 2026 00:27:03 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Untitled]]></title><description><![CDATA[/]]></description><link>root/untitled.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">root/Untitled.md</guid><pubDate>Wed, 03 Jun 2026 23:19:30 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Until Dawn 2]]></title><link>root/until-dawn-2.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">root/Until Dawn 2.md</guid><pubDate>Tue, 02 Jun 2026 21:51:03 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Silent Hill townfall]]></title><link>root/silent-hill-townfall.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">root/Silent Hill townfall.md</guid><pubDate>Tue, 02 Jun 2026 21:33:06 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[